# Documentation

## Configuration Options

### OpenAI Settings
- `openai_api_key`: Your OpenAI API key (required)
- `model`: GPT model to use (default: gpt-4o-mini)

### Server Settings
- `listening_port`: Port for Flask server (default: 5000)
- `max_audio_size_mb`: Maximum audio file size (default: 25 MB)

### Language & Voice
- `language`: Primary language (vi/en/zh/ja)
- `stt_language`: Speech-to-text language
- `tts_voice`: Text-to-speech voice (nova/alloy/echo/fable/onyx/shimmer)

### Content Filtering
- `enable_word_filter`: Enable inappropriate word filtering
- `bad_words`: List of words to filter
- `enable_educational_mode`: Enable educational responses
- `politeness_level`: Response politeness (low/medium/high)

## API Endpoints

### POST /api/chat
Main endpoint for voice interaction.

**Request:**
- Method: POST
- Content-Type: multipart/form-data
- Body:
  - `audio`: Audio file (required if no text)
  - `text`: Text input (required if no audio)
  - `session_id`: Session identifier (optional)

**Response:**
- Content-Type: audio/mpeg
- Body: MP3 audio file with response

### POST /api/reset
Reset conversation history.

**Request:**
```json
{
  "session_id": "student_001"
}
